    "spatial", "boulder-leehill-rd", "post-flood", "lidar", "post_DSM.tif"
)

# Open raster
data = rasterio.open(raster_path)

# Print metadata
print("CRS:", data.crs)
print("NoData value:", data.nodata)
print("Spatial resolution (x, y):", data.res)

In[34]:
plt.figure(figsize=(8,6))
show(data, cmap="terrain", title="Post-Flood LiDAR Digital Surface Model (DSM)")
plt.show()

The printed CRS defines the coordinate system of the LiDAR dataset. For Boulder, Colorado, a correct CRS should be in a projected coordinate system such as UTM Zone 13N (EPSG:32613), using meters as units. This is ideal for elevation and distance calculations. If the CRS were unprojected (EPSG:4326), reprojecting would be necessary before spatial analysis.
